Package bacnet.datamodel.proteomics

Class NTermCreateData

java.lang.Object
bacnet.datamodel.proteomics.NTermCreateData
public class NTermCreateData extends Object
Transform excel table describing all N-Terminal peptides found in Listeria
  • Find the position of each peptide in Listeria genome
  • create a NGS data from it
    • Author:
    christophebecavin

      Check PATHARRAY and had columns if needed

      Two types of array are possible: one with only one experiment (contains only one column with "# spectra") one with only multiple experiments (contains many columns containing "# spectra")

      For The first type:
      Check if PATHARRAY table is complete = has 8 columns, first column is the list of peptide, soluble and insoluble contains "TRUE" and "FALSE" and no "yes"
      Change "TRUE" and "FALSE" to "yes" and "no" Remove line with NH2-free peptide

      For the second type:

      • modifyPathArray

        public void modifyPathArray()
        Check PATHARRAY and had columns if needed

        Two types of array are possible:
      • one with only one experiment (contains only one column with "# spectra")
      • one with only multiple experiments (contains many columns containing "# spectra")

        For The first type:
        Check if PATHARRAY table is complete = has 8 columns, first column is the list of peptide, soluble and insoluble contains "TRUE" and "FALSE" and no "yes"
      • Change "TRUE" and "FALSE" to "yes" and "no"
      • Remove line with NH2-free peptide

        For the second type:
